  value += 1;
});
```

However, this style guide forbids modifying the value of an element.

What's the recommended way to change a property of all elements in an array? I'm working with changing the `.style` of DOM nodes in an array, so using `.map()` doesn't really feel right to me...

On line 15.3, "Use shortcuts" on the airbnb.io it says:
http://airbnb.io/javascript/#comparison--shortcuts

```
// bad
if (collection.length > 0) {
  // ...stuff...
}

// good
if (collection.length) {
  // ...stuff...
}
```

But on the github page, it is reversed:
https://github.com/airbnb/javascript#comparison--if

```
// bad
if (collection.length) {
  // ...stuff...
}

// good
if (collection.length > 0) {
  // ...stuff...
}
```

Which is the correct one?

